    "causal_summary": "The `system-spec-kit` feature catalog is the canonical, operator-facing inventory of the Spec Kit Memory MCP server's behaviors. It has fallen behind the shipped runtime: the 013 memory-index-scan roadmap delivered checkpoint-v2 file-based snapshots (schema v29), the post-insert enrichment marker (schema v30), and the MCP launcher front-proxy, while the 128 work introduced the sk-git worktree convention. None of these are discoverable from the catalog, and the scattered error-code mentions (E429, -32001, -32002) are not unified anywhere. This packet expands and registers six catalog deltas so operators can find and reason about the shipped behaviors. It edits only `feature_catalog/` content — no runtime code.",
